(registered 2017-05-09, last updated 2017-05-09)

Scheme name: mongodb
 
Status: provisional

Scheme syntax:
   mongodb://[username:password@]host1[:port1][,host2[:port2],...[,hostN[:portN]]][/[database][?options]]

   The options are given in a query string fashion and are documentated in
   the mongodb manual (see references).

Scheme semantics:
   Connecting to a mongodb server, mongodb replica set or mongodb sharded
   cluster

Encoding considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.

Applications/protocols that use this scheme name:
   mongodb <https://www.mongodb.com/>
   Related software and tools (libraries for connecting and/or exploring
   mongodb databases)

Interoperability considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.
   May be unsuitable for open use on the public internet.

Security considerations:
   Unknown, use with care.
   May be unsuitable for open use on the public internet.

Contact:
   Registering party: Ignacio Losiggio <iglosiggio&gmail.com>
   Scheme creator: Mongo DB, Inc <https://www.mongodb.com/es/contact>

Author/Change controller:
   Either the registering party or someone who is verified to represent
   the scheme creator.  See previous answer.

References:
   https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/connection-string/, https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/MongoDB